Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves examining preference models, which can be seen as a problem in data structures (cs.DS). Additionally, the paper deals with intertemporal choice, which is a topic in economics and game theory, making cs.EC (Economics and Computation) a likely sub-category. Finally, the paper involves analyzing algorithms for active learning, which can be seen as a problem in computational complexity (cs.CC).
